Notes:

@enumerate
@item @ilc{1}
The single @code{#} indicates WB.
@item @ilc{2}
The double @code{#} indicates CHAMP.
@item @ilc{3}
The comparison function and its containing brackets are printed only if it is not @code{compare}.
@item @ilc{4}
That is, a tilde followed by the printed representation of the complemented set.
@item @ilc{5}
The comparison functions are printed only if they are not @code{compare}.  If both of them are
@code{compare}, the brackets are also omitted.
@item @ilc{6}
The default, and the leading slash marking it, are printed only if it is not @code{nil}; if the
collection has no default, @code{/[no default]} is printed.
@item @ilc{7}
Char seqs --- seqs containing only characters --- are printed as strings preceded by @code{#},
possibly also suffixed with a slash and default, or @code{/[no default]}.  Within a non-char seq,
runs of consecutive characters are printed as @code{#$} followed by the characters as a string.
@end enumerate

